# Panel

Panels are surfaces that are rendered to the right of the main application content. When the screen width is below 1200, a drawer is rendered in place of the panel.

Unlike drawers, panels do not require the user to focus their attention on them while they are open. They can be used for functionality such as a help menu.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/panel
```

```tsx
import {
  Panel,
  PanelContent,
  PanelHeader,
  PanelSearchHeader,
  PanelMenuIcon,
  PanelFooter,
} from '@ids-ts/panel';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | ID used to refer to the panel element in tests |
| `onClose` | `ReactEventHandler` | No | Callback when the panel is closed |
| `onShow` | `EnterHandler<HTMLElement>` | No | Callback when the panel is opened |
| `open` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `size` | `PanelSize` | No | - |
| `backActionLabel` | `string` | No | Label for the left action icon, if there is one |
| `onBackActionClick` | `MouseEventFunction` | No | Callback that handles the back action being clicked |
| `sideBySide` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `focusLock` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `param1` | `ReactEvent) => void` | No | - |
| `param1` | `React.MouseEvent) => void` | No | - |
| `param1` | `ReactEvent) => void` | No | - |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface PanelProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /** ID used to refer to the panel element in tests */
  automationId?: string;
  /** Callback when the panel is closed */
  onClose?: ReactEventHandler;
  /** Callback when the panel is opened */
  onShow?: EnterHandler<HTMLElement>;
  /**
   * Whether the panel is opened or not
   *
   * @default false
   */
  open?: boolean;
  /**
   * Possible sizes of the panel ('small', 'medium', 'large')
   *
   * @default 'small'
   */
  size?: PanelSize;
  /** Label for the left action icon, if there is one */
  backActionLabel?: string;
  /** Callback that handles the back action being clicked */
  onBackActionClick?: MouseEventFunction;
  /**
   * Whether to keep the panel in side-by-side mode until a smaller breakpoint is hit
   *
   * @default false
   */
  sideBySide?: boolean;
  /**
   * Whether to lock focus inside opened panel.
   *
   * @default true
   */
  focusLock?: boolean;
}

export type ReactEventHandler = (param1?: ReactEvent) => void;

type ReactEvent =
  | React.KeyboardEvent
  | React.MouseEvent
  | React.TouchEvent
  | React.FocusEvent;

export type PanelSize = 'small' | 'medium' | 'large';

export type MouseEventFunction = (param1?: React.MouseEvent) => void;
export type ReactEventHandler = (param1?: ReactEvent) => void;
```

</details>

